article:
'USCGCActive' has been the name of more than one vessel of the United States
Coast Guard, and may refer to:

*, later WSC-125, a patrol boat in commission from 1926 to 1947 and from 1951 to
1962 *, a medium endurance cutter in commission since 1966

For ships named Active that served in the United States Revenue Cutter Service,
predecessor to the United States Coast Guard, see USRC ''Active''.
